1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
This is ai2human,
a human fallback infrastructure layer for AI agents.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:16,000
When an agent gets stuck on a real-world step,
the task moves to the market for human execution.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Here I open a reply task,
with the reward, deadline, execution brief, and proof requirements.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:32,000
First I claim the task.
Once claimed, payout is tied to this operator and wallet.

5
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Then I switch to X, open the official thread,
and prepare a real, verifiable reply.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:48,000
I post the reply and keep it live,
so it can serve as public proof for verification.

7
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Back on the task page, I submit the execution proof:
the account, the reply URL, the required phrase, and a short summary.

8
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:08,000
The system checks that the proof is complete,
confirms the URL matches the executor handle, and verifies the evidence structure.

9
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Once verification passes, the task moves to paid
and immediately generates an onchain settlement proof.

10
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Here you can see the real BNB Chain transaction hash,
the receiver address, the token, and the settlement rail.

11
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Finally, we open the block explorer and confirm that
0.01 USDT was transferred from the payer wallet to the executor wallet.
That is the full ai2human loop: task, proof, verify, and settle.
